15 SECTION 2.
16 Said part is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
17 "10-1-393.20.
18 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
19 (1) 'Assessment task' means any assignment, essay, thesis, dissertation, report,
20 examination, project, or other assessable part of a course of study assigned or otherwise
21 given to a student or examinee for credit.
22 (2) 'Assignor' means:
23 (A) Any local school system or public school, private school, or home study program
24 in this state;
25 (B) Any institution of the University System of Georgia or unit of the Technical
26 College System of Georgia;
27 (C) Any organization that issues a professional license in this state; or
28 (D) Any employee or agent of such schools, programs, institutions, units, or
29 organizations.
30 (3) 'Commercial purpose' means a purpose relating to financial gain or other
31 compensation.
32 (4) 'For credit' means for evaluation by an assignor as a factor in the issuance of any
33 grade, evaluation, degree, diploma, certification, certificate, credential, exam score, or
34 professional license.
35 (5) 'Home study program' means a home study program as defined in subsection (c) of
36 Code Section 20-2-690.
37 (6) 'Person' means any individual, partnership, firm, limited liability company,
38 association, corporation, or other legal entity or unincorporated organization.
39 (7) 'Private school' shall have the same meaning as private school set forth in
40 subsection (b) of Code Section 20-2-690.
41 (8) 'Student or examinee' means:
