42 (A) Any student of a local school system or public school, a private school, or a home
43 study program in this state;
44 (B) Any student of an institution of the University System of Georgia or a unit of the
45 Technical College System of Georgia; or
46 (C) Any examinee for a professional license in this state.
47 (9) 'Work product' means any written, electronic, recorded, pictorial, artistic, or other
48 form of work.
49 (b) It shall be unlawful for any person, for a commercial purpose, to provide or otherwise
50 cause to be provided any work product to a student or examinee in a substantially
51 completed form that could, under the circumstances, reasonably be considered as being,
52 or forming a part of, an assessment task.
53 (c) No disclaimer or contractual language between a person providing work product and
54 a student or examinee shall exempt such person from the provisions of subsection (b) of
55 this Code section.
56 (d) Any violation of subsection (b) of this Code section shall constitute an unfair or
57 deceptive act or practice in the conduct of consumer transactions under Part 2 of Article
58 15 of this chapter, the 'Fair Business Practices Act of 1975'; provided, however, that
59 enforcement against such violations shall only be by public enforcement by the Attorney
60 General pursuant to this part and shall not be enforceable through a private right of action
61 under Code Section 10-1-399.
62 (e) Nothing in this Code section shall be construed to:
63 (1) Prohibit any person from providing tutorial assistance, research material, or general
64 information to a student or examinee; or
65 (2) Prohibit any person from providing an automated system, software, or platform that
66 generates specific responses to a student's or examinee's prompts; provided, however, that
67 such responses shall not constitute a substantially completed assessment task and the
